<Page x:Class="AsynAwaitExamples.Steps.Step14_Deadlocks"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:AsynAwaitExamples.ViewModels"
      Title="Step 14 - Deadlocks">
    <Page.DataContext>
        <vm:Step14ViewModel/>
    </Page.DataContext>
    <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
        <StackPanel Margin="10">
            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HeaderStyle}" 
                       Text="Step 14: Deadlocks &amp; .Result/.Wait() Anti-Patterns"/>

            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource ExplanationStyle}" xml:space="preserve">DEADLOCKS: The #1 real-world mistake with async code.

Calling .Result or .Wait() on the UI thread BLOCKS the thread. But the
awaited continuation needs that same thread to resume (because of the
SynchronizationContext). Both sides wait for each other = DEADLOCK!

This is like standing in a narrow doorway waiting for someone to come
through, while they are on the other side waiting for YOU to move.

RULE: NEVER use .Result or .Wait() on the UI thread.
ALWAYS use "await" instead. It releases the thread so the continuation can run.</TextBlock>

            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="? The CORRECT way (await)"
                    Command="{Binding CorrectWayCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? .Result on a background thread (safe but not ideal)"
                    Command="{Binding ResultOnBackgroundThreadCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? Explain the deadlock step-by-step"
                    Command="{Binding ShowDeadlockExplanationCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? ConfigureAwait(false) as escape hatch"
                    Command="{Binding ConfigureAwaitEscapeCommand}"/>

            <TextBox Style="{StaticResource OutputStyle}" Height="300"
                     Text="{Binding OutputText, Mode=OneWay}"/>
        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Page>
